body:
@eribeiro Good point :)
@gwenshap Thanks for the quick review - have you seen this? @ijuma posted merge instructions for github here: https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/Patch+submission+and+review#Patchsubmissionandreview-MergingGitHubPullRequests

And also this:
https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/Contributing+Code+Changes

@granders, can you change the PR name to something that matches our standard? It looks like the merge script automatically uses the PR name as the commit comment, so we need something like:
"KAFKA-2327; broker doesn't start if config defines advertised.host but not advertised.port"

Or @ijuma can modify the script to allow editing the commit message :)
